      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That perspective is philosophically known as nihilism, and it is completely valid to feel despair when confronted with that cosmic scale. However, even if the play ends someday, the participants in it still feel the emotions, taste the food, and create memories during the performance. The value isn't in the eternity of the scene, but in the intense, specific reality of experiencing it right now. You don't have to believe in a grand cosmic point to find a personal one in the shared human experience of feeling something deeply.",
