      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Opting out might offer a strange kind of peace, but many find that the resistance itself gives their fleeting experiences texture and significance in moments that will eventually be forgotten anyway. The struggle doesn't have to feel heroic or cosmic to be meaningful; sometimes simply acknowledging the pain and trying to alleviate it, however slightly, is a powerful act of love toward oneself. Even if the ultimate destination is silence, the choice of how to travel there—whether with effort or surrender—defines the quality of the journey for the traveler themselves.",
